On Sat, 13 Apr 2002 mcardon(-at-)attglobal.net wrote:

> I was given a 1966 Corvair, the body needs a lot of work, but the engine
> runs fine. Would it be possible to install this engine in my 71 Westy? If it
> is possible, how hard would it be? Thanks in advance for any replies,

The corvair turns the wrong way for the VW transmission.  You have to
install a special camshaft to allow the corvair to turn the right way.

Most corvair installations I've seen also include the corvair
transmission, often the 2-speed powerglide automatic.

George

